## When to use
When you need to quickly check the disk usage of your system or a specific directory.

## Approach
Modify the user profile preferences file to include shell aliases that simplify running `df` and `du` commands. Use `file_write` tool from KDEV to edit the file directly.

## Example
```shell
# Add dfh alias for checking disk space in human readable format
alias dfh='df -h'
# Add duh alias for checking directory usage in human readable format
alias duh='du -sh *'
```

## Pitfalls
Ensure that no existing aliases or commands conflict with the new ones added.
